      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Originalism is a judicial philosophy that interprets the Constitution based on the original public meaning of the text at the time of its ratification, rather than evolving with modern societal values. Proponents argue this approach ensures democratic legitimacy by limiting judges from imposing their own personal policy preferences under the guise of constitutional interpretation. It is also a necessary check on judicial power, preventing the Supreme Court from acting as a super-legislature that can rewrite the fundamental law of the land whenever it suits the majority.",
